WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:03.046
- Previously on
"God Friended Me"...

00:03.090 --> 00:05.396
- Oh! Take that, old man!

00:05.440 --> 00:06.180
- Old?

00:06.223 --> 00:07.311
I'm the youngest member

00:07.355 --> 00:08.834
of the board
of your daddy's church.

00:08.878 --> 00:10.358
Yeah, that building's
gonna be a game-changer.

00:10.401 --> 00:12.142
- And everyone
in the community

00:12.186 --> 00:13.361
is pulling for you, Terrence.

00:13.404 --> 00:14.884
[all cheering]

00:14.927 --> 00:16.494
- Just want to thank everyone

00:16.538 --> 00:18.192
for coming out
and helping celebrate

00:18.235 --> 00:21.673
my aunt and uncle
on their 25th anniversary.

00:21.717 --> 00:22.979
[all cheering]

00:23.023 --> 00:23.980
- I thought you were
enjoying yourself.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.068
- I was just putting on

00:25.112 --> 00:26.069
a good face for our family.

00:26.113 --> 00:27.375
- I have it under control.

00:27.418 --> 00:29.899
Everything's gonna be fine.

00:29.942 --> 00:33.903
[lively electronic music]

00:33.946 --> 00:35.600
- ♪ We're gonna rise, rise,
rise, rise, rise ♪

00:35.644 --> 00:36.775
♪ Till we fall

00:36.819 --> 00:38.516
- Sunday morning.

00:38.560 --> 00:40.127
It means something different
to everyone.

00:40.170 --> 00:42.172
Church, brunch, football,

00:42.216 --> 00:44.957
hitting the snooze button
and waking up an hour later.

00:45.001 --> 00:46.568
Truth is,

00:46.611 --> 00:49.484
it doesn't matter how
you spend your Sunday.

00:49.527 --> 00:52.269
What matters is who
you spend your Sunday with.

00:52.313 --> 00:54.706
The people in your life.
Your village.

00:54.750 --> 00:56.665
Your friends. Your family.

00:56.708 --> 00:57.840
They're the ones behind you.

00:57.883 --> 00:59.842
The ones you count on

00:59.885 --> 01:01.191
that are always there for you.

01:01.235 --> 01:02.932
Have faith in them.

01:02.975 --> 01:05.108
Because when you do,
good things happen.

01:05.152 --> 01:06.718
- Having faith

01:06.762 --> 01:09.417
in each other

01:09.460 --> 01:11.984
is the true meaning of God.

01:12.028 --> 01:15.553
That is the reason this church
stands firmly.

01:15.597 --> 01:18.774
The reason we can build towards
a better tomorrow.

01:18.817 --> 01:21.516
The reason, I am proud to say,

01:21.559 --> 01:24.562
that Harlem Episcopal has
finally raised enough funds

01:24.606 --> 01:27.217
to build our Children's Center.

01:27.261 --> 01:30.220
[cheers and applause]

01:30.264 --> 01:33.093
♪

01:33.136 --> 01:34.920
- Oh, bam!

01:34.964 --> 01:36.444
Mmm.

01:36.487 --> 01:38.098
Arthur, that Children's Center

01:38.141 --> 01:41.144
is a major accomplishment.

01:41.188 --> 01:43.799
I'm sorry that Lena
couldn't join us today.

01:43.842 --> 01:45.801
She's feeling a little
under the weather.

01:45.844 --> 01:48.238
- Everything okay with you two?

01:48.282 --> 01:50.066
- Yeah, yeah. I mean, I know
what you saw at the party,

01:50.110 --> 01:52.155
but we're good.

01:52.199 --> 01:54.375
- Hey, guys.
- Hey. There he is.

01:54.418 --> 01:55.550
What's happening?
- Hey.

01:55.593 --> 01:57.073
- Miles, you are just in time.

01:57.117 --> 01:59.206
I am one move away from
checkmating your uncle.

01:59.249 --> 02:00.859
- Your king is unprotected.

02:00.903 --> 02:02.600
- No, sir. See,
what you call that

02:02.644 --> 02:04.515
is a strategy, okay.
- Mm-hmm.

02:04.559 --> 02:05.951
- How's the marketing class
going?

02:05.995 --> 02:07.823
- Oh, it couldn't be better.

02:07.866 --> 02:11.261
- I was, uh, unaware that you
were back in school.

02:11.305 --> 02:13.829
- Oh, it's--it's
an extension course, Dad.

02:13.872 --> 02:16.179
Uncle T hooked me up
with one of his professors.

02:16.223 --> 02:18.964
- Uh-huh.

02:19.008 --> 02:20.879
- No, no, no, no!
- Check. Mate.

02:20.923 --> 02:22.490
- Every time...
[phone ringing]

02:22.533 --> 02:26.363
You're lucky. I got this,
excuse me a second.

02:26.407 --> 02:27.930
Yep?

02:30.019 --> 02:32.326
- Look, Dad, I was gonna
tell you about the class.

02:32.369 --> 02:34.676
- Yeah. Of course.

02:37.026 --> 02:38.201
- No, no, no, no, no.

02:38.245 --> 02:40.856
That is not what we discussed.

02:40.899 --> 02:43.032
All right.
I'll be right there.

02:44.903 --> 02:46.557
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, just...

02:46.601 --> 02:48.168
just gotta head down
to the construction site

02:48.211 --> 02:49.517
and handle a couple things.

02:49.560 --> 02:51.171
Y'all keep playing.
Don't

02:51.214 --> 02:54.435
let this man win, okay?
It's bad for his ego.

02:54.478 --> 02:56.045
- He seems stressed.

02:56.088 --> 02:58.613
- Your uncle's always got
a million things going on.

02:58.656 --> 03:00.354
[chuckles]
I'm sure he will be fine.

03:00.397 --> 03:02.704
[phone buzzing]

03:02.747 --> 03:09.276
♪

03:10.320 --> 03:13.932
Everything okay?

03:16.935 --> 03:18.807
- So how'd dinner go
with Eli?

03:18.850 --> 03:21.592
- Uh, awkward at first, but...

03:21.636 --> 03:23.246
then kinda great.

03:23.290 --> 03:25.814
- You gonna see him again?

03:25.857 --> 03:27.946
- Uh...
yeah, I don't know.

03:27.990 --> 03:29.470
I'm still figuring it out.

03:29.513 --> 03:30.775
You know, it's nice
to be able to

03:30.819 --> 03:32.168
talk to you about
this kind of stuff.

03:32.212 --> 03:34.083
- It's nice to be here
and listen.

03:34.126 --> 03:35.693
- Care Bear.

03:35.737 --> 03:36.694
- Dad?

03:36.738 --> 03:38.218
- Surprise.

03:38.261 --> 03:41.264
I would have called,
but this is more...

03:41.308 --> 03:43.266
- Hello, Jeffrey.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.659
- Susan.

03:44.702 --> 03:48.140
♪

03:48.184 --> 03:50.708
- [sighing] God, you should
have seen his face.

03:50.752 --> 03:52.319
And her face.
- I'm surprised you didn't

03:52.362 --> 03:53.755
tell your dad, I thought
you two were close.

03:53.798 --> 03:55.191
- Yeah, well, we are.

03:55.235 --> 03:57.106
But could you imagine
that phone call?

03:57.149 --> 03:58.542
"Hey, Dad,
remember the woman who

03:58.586 --> 04:00.327
"Left us and never came back,

04:00.370 --> 04:02.242
"Broke your heart into,
like, a million little pieces?

04:02.285 --> 04:03.286
"Well, actually,
we've been hanging out

04:03.330 --> 04:04.809
"And like, totally bonding.

04:04.853 --> 04:06.028
How are things with you?"

04:06.071 --> 04:07.508
- I wouldn't lead with that.

04:07.551 --> 04:09.292
- Can I just
say something here?

04:09.336 --> 04:13.731
It is truly refreshing
to see someone else spiral.

04:13.775 --> 04:15.472
So thank you.

04:15.516 --> 04:17.692
Oh, by the way, I sent
the God account's new firewall

04:17.735 --> 04:19.302
to this old friend of mine.

04:19.346 --> 04:20.825
If anybody can help
crack it, it's her.

04:20.869 --> 04:22.784
- Good, because whoever's
behind the God account

04:22.827 --> 04:23.872
really upped their game.

04:23.915 --> 04:25.308
I got a new friend suggestion.

04:25.352 --> 04:26.527
It's for my Uncle Terrence.

04:26.570 --> 04:28.224
Thing is,
we're already friends.

04:28.268 --> 04:31.314
- God account's
getting personal.

04:31.358 --> 04:33.534
- This is the first time
you've gotten a suggestion

04:33.577 --> 04:35.710
for someone you know.

04:35.753 --> 04:37.538
Do you have any idea

04:37.581 --> 04:38.756
why they would have
sent you his name?

04:38.800 --> 04:40.367
- No. Terrence
is one of the most

04:40.410 --> 04:42.151
important people in my life.

04:42.194 --> 04:43.457
And yet, somehow
the God account

04:43.500 --> 04:45.197
knows something is wrong
before I do?

04:45.241 --> 04:48.157
- Well, it's a good thing
you got his name, then.

04:48.200 --> 04:50.028
You could figure out
how to help him.

04:50.072 --> 04:52.204
♪

04:55.469 --> 04:58.472
[indistinct chatter]

05:01.083 --> 05:02.302
- Nephew.

05:02.345 --> 05:03.651
Ha ha!

05:03.694 --> 05:05.217
- You in the big leagues now,
Uncle T!

05:05.261 --> 05:06.393
- Pretty impressive, huh?

05:06.436 --> 05:07.916
- It looks amazing, really.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.178
- For the people who live here

05:09.221 --> 05:10.788
built by the people
who live here.

05:10.832 --> 05:12.616
Money stays right here

05:12.660 --> 05:13.704
and it's all good
for the community.

05:13.748 --> 05:15.445
What's happening, baby?

05:15.489 --> 05:16.664
- Uh...

05:16.707 --> 05:18.709
You, um, remember I told you

05:18.753 --> 05:19.884
about the God account?

05:19.928 --> 05:21.799
- Yeah.

05:21.843 --> 05:25.150
- Well.

05:25.194 --> 05:26.935
- [chuckling]

05:26.978 --> 05:27.936
You gotta be kidding me.

05:27.979 --> 05:29.154
- Uncle T.

05:29.198 --> 05:30.373
You and me, we have always been

05:30.417 --> 05:33.463
honest with each other.

05:33.507 --> 05:37.032
Is there something
you want to tell me?

05:40.731 --> 05:41.950
- We should talk.

05:48.696 --> 05:50.045
- So how does this
usually work?

05:50.088 --> 05:51.394
- Well, it's different
every time,

05:51.438 --> 05:52.395
but you're the first
friend suggestion

05:52.439 --> 05:53.614
I actually know.

05:53.657 --> 05:55.137
- And they sent you
my name when?

05:55.180 --> 05:58.575
- Right after you took off
from the park.

05:58.619 --> 06:01.404
Hey, you got a phone call
right before that,

06:01.448 --> 06:02.797
something about work

06:02.840 --> 06:03.798
and you seemed pretty stressed.

06:03.841 --> 06:04.799
Is everything okay?

06:04.842 --> 06:06.017
- That was a permit issue.

06:06.061 --> 06:07.236
I mean, that's already
been fixed.

06:07.279 --> 06:09.325
But truthfully,

06:09.369 --> 06:11.893
things have been
really stressful at work.

06:11.936 --> 06:13.416
- Terrence.

06:13.460 --> 06:16.027
- Conrad. Ah, meet my nephew,
Miles Finer.

06:16.071 --> 06:18.116
- Reverend Finer's boy,
of course.

06:18.160 --> 06:20.162
Your father's been a role model
in our community

06:20.205 --> 06:21.250
since I can remember.

06:21.293 --> 06:23.121
- Oh, well, thank you, man.

06:23.165 --> 06:25.776
- Yeah, your uncle here
ain't too far behind.

06:25.820 --> 06:27.517
That high-rise he's building,

06:27.561 --> 06:29.127
that's gonna change things.

06:29.171 --> 06:30.172
If you ever need anything,

06:30.215 --> 06:31.173
give me a call.

06:31.216 --> 06:32.653
- No doubt.

06:32.696 --> 06:35.090
- All right, you two enjoy your
Sunday.

06:35.133 --> 06:36.265
- You as well.

06:36.308 --> 06:37.353
- Who's that?

06:37.397 --> 06:39.790
- This dude I grew up with.

06:39.834 --> 06:43.620
Listen, I want to talk
to you, though, about...

06:43.664 --> 06:45.796
something, and I want
to make sure that you

06:45.840 --> 06:47.711
hear it from me directly.

06:47.755 --> 06:50.192
- Hmm?
- Your Auntie Lena.

06:50.235 --> 06:53.151
She's asked me for a divorce.

06:53.195 --> 06:57.373
- Wait, I'm...

06:57.417 --> 06:59.375
I don't understand.

06:59.419 --> 07:02.291
You guys just celebrated
25 years together

07:02.334 --> 07:05.076
and now all of the sudden
she's asking for a divorce?

07:05.120 --> 07:07.252
- It's my fault.

07:07.296 --> 07:09.298
Spend way too much time
at the construction site

07:09.341 --> 07:10.604
and not enough time
with my wife.

07:10.647 --> 07:12.257
- Then just talk to her.

07:12.301 --> 07:14.042
Okay, let her know that
things got away from you

07:14.085 --> 07:16.305
and that you're going to
spend time with her.

07:16.348 --> 07:18.002
- I plan on doing
more of that.

07:18.046 --> 07:20.918
But I gotta get
this construction complete.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.964
- No. No, you can't wait.

07:23.007 --> 07:24.269
- I know it sounds crazy.

07:24.313 --> 07:26.228
It's selfish, I know,
because it is.

07:26.271 --> 07:27.664
But listen.

07:27.708 --> 07:31.015
I've been working
my entire life to get here.

07:31.059 --> 07:32.190
This is my shot

07:32.234 --> 07:33.583
at a seat at the table.

07:33.627 --> 07:35.411
I got a chance to make my mark
on this city.

07:35.455 --> 07:39.328
To build something that will
stand the test of time.

07:39.371 --> 07:44.594
Look, I just have to see
this through completion.

07:44.638 --> 07:47.510
And I know I can--

07:47.554 --> 07:52.036
I know I can get Lena back.

07:52.080 --> 07:55.562
So your friend suggestion
or not,

07:55.605 --> 08:00.218
I gotta do this my way.

08:00.262 --> 08:01.393
- Yeah, I'm sorry
you had to find out

08:01.437 --> 08:02.569
about Mom like that.

08:02.612 --> 08:04.571
- Well, to be honest, um...

08:04.614 --> 08:06.834
I knew the two of you
have reconnected.

08:06.877 --> 08:08.923
It's sort of why I'm here.

08:08.966 --> 08:11.012
- You read my article.

08:11.055 --> 08:12.535
Why didn't you say anything?

08:12.579 --> 08:13.971
- Well, I figured
since you didn't bring it up

08:14.015 --> 08:14.972
you weren't ready
to talk about it.

08:15.016 --> 08:15.973
And I wanted to give you

08:16.017 --> 08:17.801
the space you needed.

08:17.845 --> 08:20.195
But I couldn't stop
worrying about you.

08:20.238 --> 08:21.675
- Hey, I'm--

08:21.718 --> 08:25.156
I'm sorry I didn't tell you.

08:25.200 --> 08:26.767
I guess it's just...

08:26.810 --> 08:28.595
when I tell you things,
that's when they become real.

08:28.638 --> 08:32.468
And I wasn't really sure
I was ready for that.

08:32.512 --> 08:34.252
- You know,
when you were growing up

08:34.296 --> 08:37.168
I would ask you every question
under the sun.

08:37.212 --> 08:39.562
But I never brought up
your mother.

08:39.606 --> 08:41.912
And that's on me.

08:41.956 --> 08:44.828
I want you to know you can
talk to me about her.

08:44.872 --> 08:47.222
- I'm glad.

08:47.265 --> 08:49.267
- But I do need
to ask you something.

08:49.311 --> 08:51.182
- Okay?

08:51.226 --> 08:52.619
- Is Susan sober?

08:52.662 --> 08:55.404
- Dad. Yes.

08:55.447 --> 08:57.362
For a long time now.

08:57.406 --> 08:58.842
- I had to ask.

08:58.886 --> 09:01.192
- I know how much
she hurt you.

09:01.236 --> 09:03.499
The both of us.

09:03.543 --> 09:05.588
So I know you'll never
really be okay with this

09:05.632 --> 09:08.025
unless you talk to her.

09:08.069 --> 09:10.854
See for yourself
how much she's changed.

09:10.898 --> 09:13.553
Maybe we could all
have dinner or something?

09:13.596 --> 09:14.945
- Fine.

09:14.989 --> 09:16.338
But make it lunch.

09:16.381 --> 09:18.732
I want dinner to be
the two of us.

09:18.775 --> 09:23.127
♪

09:23.171 --> 09:24.868
- They can't be splitting up.

09:24.912 --> 09:27.175
I mean, they're Aunt Lena
and Uncle T.

09:27.218 --> 09:28.611
- That's what I said.

09:28.655 --> 09:29.612
- I'm gonna head over
to Lena's tomorrow

09:29.656 --> 09:31.179
and check in on her.

09:31.222 --> 09:32.746
- Hey, well, what am I
supposed to do, Al?

09:32.789 --> 09:35.183
Uncle T said that he does not
want my help.

09:35.226 --> 09:36.880
But I cannot turn my back
on family.

09:36.924 --> 09:38.534
- Are you asking your sister

09:38.578 --> 09:39.535
or the therapist?

09:39.579 --> 09:41.319
- Both.

09:41.363 --> 09:43.713
- Well, your sister would say

09:43.757 --> 09:45.541
you should stay the hell
out of it.

09:45.585 --> 09:46.890
I mean, Miles,
they've been married

09:46.934 --> 09:47.935
for 25 years

09:47.978 --> 09:49.110
and don't need their nephew

09:49.153 --> 09:50.807
solving their
marriage problems.

09:50.851 --> 09:52.940
- Okay, so what does
the therapist say?

09:52.983 --> 09:54.550
- She says

09:54.594 --> 09:56.204
you've put your uncle
on a pedestal

09:56.247 --> 09:58.119
your entire life.

09:58.162 --> 09:59.207
Now you're scared
of finding out

09:59.250 --> 10:01.992
he's anything but perfect.

10:02.036 --> 10:06.431
♪

10:06.475 --> 10:10.348
Marriages don't end
on a whim, Miles.

10:10.392 --> 10:11.436
- Your point?

10:11.480 --> 10:13.656
- That there's obviously

10:13.700 --> 10:14.657
some things going on

10:14.701 --> 10:16.354
that we don't know about.

10:16.398 --> 10:19.444
Things maybe they don't want
us to know about.

10:19.488 --> 10:21.403
I mean, some things
just can't be fixed.

10:21.446 --> 10:23.753
- But why did the God account
send me Terrence's name?

10:23.797 --> 10:25.233
- I don't know.

10:25.276 --> 10:26.451
Maybe there's something else
in his life

10:26.495 --> 10:29.541
you're supposed
to help him with.

10:31.282 --> 10:32.675
Well...

10:32.719 --> 10:34.895
that's all the time
we have here today.

10:34.938 --> 10:37.201
Oh, and don't forget
the ceremony

10:37.245 --> 10:38.376
for the new Children's Center.

10:38.420 --> 10:39.639
Dad would love
to see you there.

10:39.682 --> 10:41.510
- Yeah, I'll be there.

10:41.553 --> 10:42.859
- All right, bro,
see you later.

10:42.903 --> 10:44.078
- Okay.

10:48.082 --> 10:50.867
[thoughtful music]

10:50.911 --> 10:52.434
So did your hacker friend

10:52.477 --> 10:54.436
give you some insight
on the God account?

10:54.479 --> 10:55.742
- Over email?
- Yeah.

10:55.785 --> 10:57.265
- Are you insane?

10:57.308 --> 10:59.049
Hackers are
a paranoid bunch, bro.

10:59.093 --> 11:01.138
Not sure why.
- Maybe because

11:01.182 --> 11:04.315
they're engaged in
criminal activity?

11:04.359 --> 11:07.231
- Not all hackers are involved
in something illegal, Cara.

11:07.275 --> 11:08.755
Some of us just enjoy coding.

11:08.798 --> 11:10.365
- Right. Sorry.

11:10.408 --> 11:13.760
I'm just tense about lunch
with Mom and Dad.

11:13.803 --> 11:15.892
Mom and Dad. That is so weird
to say out loud.

11:15.936 --> 11:17.285
- Hey, you're doing
the right thing, you know?

11:17.328 --> 11:18.460
Don't worry about it.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.027
- Maybe you're right.

11:20.070 --> 11:21.637
But how are you holding up?

11:21.681 --> 11:23.552
I mean, your aunt and uncle
splitting must be tough.

11:23.595 --> 11:25.336
- Well, Ali said that
I should stay out of it.

11:25.380 --> 11:27.121
- Right, but you're not
going to.

11:27.164 --> 11:28.775
- Definitely not going to.

11:28.818 --> 11:31.473
- No, no, Terrence has always
been there for me.

11:31.516 --> 11:33.605
And I know how much
he loves my aunt.

11:33.649 --> 11:35.390
This must be the reason
why the God account

11:35.433 --> 11:36.391
sent me his name.

11:36.434 --> 11:38.785
- Here you go.

11:38.828 --> 11:40.134
So who are you guys
waiting for?

11:40.177 --> 11:41.396
- Rakesh's hacker friend,

11:41.439 --> 11:43.267
that's if she ever shows up.

11:43.311 --> 11:44.616
- Yeah, how do you
know her again?

11:44.660 --> 11:46.531
- Uh, we met at MIT.

11:46.575 --> 11:48.838
And trust me, she's legit.

11:48.882 --> 11:50.622
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

11:50.666 --> 11:52.059
- Wait, there she is right now.

11:52.102 --> 11:53.321
Let me do the talking, okay?

11:53.364 --> 11:54.322
She can get intense.

11:54.365 --> 11:56.193
So no eye contact.

11:56.237 --> 11:57.194
No sudden moves.

11:57.238 --> 11:58.587
None of that.

12:00.502 --> 12:02.069
- Ramen-Rakesh.

12:02.112 --> 12:05.072
- Lemonhead-Lucy.

12:05.115 --> 12:08.379
♪

12:08.423 --> 12:11.426
- [laughing]

12:13.036 --> 12:15.169
- I was just messing
with you guys.

12:16.344 --> 12:18.259
This is Cara, that's Miles.
- Hey.

12:18.302 --> 12:19.695
- Rakesh said he had "friends."

12:19.739 --> 12:20.783
I had to see it
with my own eyes.

12:20.827 --> 12:21.784
- Ha-ha.

12:21.828 --> 12:22.916
- So were you able to crack

12:22.959 --> 12:23.917
the firewall he sent you?

12:23.960 --> 12:25.048
- No.

12:25.092 --> 12:26.093
Whoever designed it

12:26.136 --> 12:27.703
has some serious game.

12:27.747 --> 12:29.096
You ever hear of Falken?

12:29.139 --> 12:30.575
- Uh, yeah.

12:30.619 --> 12:33.361
He's only the most
badass hacker ever.

12:33.404 --> 12:34.884
He was developing
a new computer language

12:34.928 --> 12:36.538
known as predictive code.

12:36.581 --> 12:39.280
It's basically the
building blocks of real AI.

12:39.323 --> 12:40.716
- And then, about ten years
ago, he just vanished.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.370
Went off the grid.

12:42.413 --> 12:43.893
- So you think the code was
written by this Falken guy?

12:43.937 --> 12:44.938
- It's possible.

12:44.981 --> 12:46.069
Give me a day.

12:46.113 --> 12:47.810
Let me put out a few feelers.

12:47.854 --> 12:49.029
Maybe someone knows what rock

12:49.072 --> 12:50.944
he's been hiding under.

12:50.987 --> 12:52.423
- What is it?

12:52.467 --> 12:54.774
- That's my Aunt Lena.

12:54.817 --> 12:56.514
I'll be right back.

12:58.386 --> 12:59.822
Aunt Lena.
- Miles.

12:59.866 --> 13:01.084
- What are you doing here?
- [chuckles]

13:01.128 --> 13:02.956
I came down
to speak with Ali.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.218
I was gonna find you next.

13:04.261 --> 13:06.960
- Is everything okay?

13:07.003 --> 13:10.833
- I'm gonna be, uh, staying
with my sister for a while.

13:10.877 --> 13:12.661
I'm headed upstate tomorrow.

13:12.704 --> 13:16.143
- Look, Aunt Lena, Uncle T
knows that it is his fault.

13:16.186 --> 13:18.232
Okay? He still loves you.

13:18.275 --> 13:22.018
- And I love him, but sometimes
that's not enough.

13:22.062 --> 13:25.152
I know you've always
looked up to him, Miles.

13:25.195 --> 13:26.283
- Aunt Lena.

13:26.327 --> 13:29.330
Please. Please.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.201
He can fix this.

13:31.245 --> 13:35.466
- No. He can't.

13:35.510 --> 13:38.121
He's made decisions
that have jeopardized

13:38.165 --> 13:40.384
everything we built together.

13:40.428 --> 13:43.866
I'm sorry, Miles.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.781
Oh.

13:47.609 --> 13:50.568
Take care, sweetheart.

13:50.612 --> 13:52.614
- Hey.

13:52.657 --> 13:56.487
♪

13:56.531 --> 13:57.488
- No, no, no, no.

13:57.532 --> 13:58.620
Listen to me.

13:58.663 --> 14:00.883
The problem was with payroll.

14:00.927 --> 14:02.798
Okay? Your guys
are gonna get paid.

14:02.842 --> 14:04.104
I just need a little more time.

14:04.147 --> 14:05.627
- That's what you've said
for two weeks.

14:05.670 --> 14:06.802
I'm putting them
on another job.

14:06.846 --> 14:07.847
- Come on, Tom. Tom.

14:07.890 --> 14:09.457
Y-You can't do this to me.

14:09.500 --> 14:11.285
You--Tommy!

14:13.417 --> 14:14.897
- Uncle T, what's going on?

14:14.941 --> 14:16.464
- Miles, now is not the time.

14:16.507 --> 14:17.900
- Yeah, I can see that.

14:17.944 --> 14:19.336
Come on, talk to me.

14:19.380 --> 14:21.991
Uncle T, I just talked
to Auntie Lena.

14:24.037 --> 14:25.560
Now whatever is going on,

14:25.603 --> 14:27.779
you can tell me.

14:27.823 --> 14:29.912
- [chuckles]

14:35.178 --> 14:36.484
I'm broke.

14:38.921 --> 14:41.576
I'm broke.

14:41.619 --> 14:44.492
I mean, I put every dime
I have into this.

14:44.535 --> 14:46.146
I've...

14:46.189 --> 14:49.323
mortgaged my house...

14:49.366 --> 14:52.021
Maxed out every...

14:52.065 --> 14:53.370
line of credit.
And the problems

14:53.414 --> 14:54.894
just keep coming.

14:54.937 --> 14:57.548
And coming and coming
and coming.

14:57.592 --> 15:00.682
♪

15:00.725 --> 15:02.989
I can't make the next
bank payment.

15:03.032 --> 15:07.863
♪

15:07.907 --> 15:10.648
It's over.

15:10.692 --> 15:12.737
- Well, maybe there's
something else you can do.

15:12.781 --> 15:14.130
You can take out a loan...

15:14.174 --> 15:17.177
- Oh, no, no, no.
I'm so far

15:17.220 --> 15:20.615
underwater, I mean,
nobody wants to touch me.

15:20.658 --> 15:23.052
That call I got this morning
was from the bank.

15:23.096 --> 15:25.968
I asked for an extension and...

15:26.012 --> 15:27.883
no.

15:27.927 --> 15:30.886
♪

15:30.930 --> 15:33.541
They're gonna take it.

15:36.544 --> 15:38.372
You know, after everything
that I've done,

15:38.415 --> 15:40.243
after...

15:40.287 --> 15:43.812
all the sacrifices...

15:43.855 --> 15:47.685
with Lena...

15:47.729 --> 15:50.471
It's gone.

15:50.514 --> 15:56.564
♪

15:56.607 --> 15:59.567
[soft music]

15:59.610 --> 16:06.617
♪

16:12.493 --> 16:14.190
- How's Uncle Terrence doing?
- Devastated.

16:14.234 --> 16:16.627
- So what's he gonna do?
- I don't know.

16:16.671 --> 16:18.890
I mean, the bank
is gonna foreclose today.

16:18.934 --> 16:20.675
And I can't just sit back
and do nothing.

16:20.718 --> 16:22.024
There must be something
I can do.

16:22.068 --> 16:23.547
- I know you want to help him.

16:23.591 --> 16:25.201
But the kind of trouble
that he's in,

16:25.245 --> 16:26.855
you can't get him out of.

16:26.898 --> 16:29.945
- Then why would the
God account send me his name?

16:29.989 --> 16:32.208
There has to be a way.

16:32.252 --> 16:34.080
Maybe I can go
talk to the bank.

16:34.123 --> 16:35.472
See if they would give him
another loan.

16:35.516 --> 16:38.040
- There is someone
you need to talk to.

16:38.084 --> 16:41.913
But it's not the bank.

16:41.957 --> 16:43.350
- I'm sorry to drop in
on you like this, Dad.

16:43.393 --> 16:44.655
- Please.

16:44.699 --> 16:46.179
To what do I owe the pleasure?

16:46.222 --> 16:47.528
- Hey.

16:47.571 --> 16:48.572
There he is,

16:48.616 --> 16:50.400
my favorite nephew.

16:50.444 --> 16:51.967
- What are you doing here?

16:52.011 --> 16:53.099
- Terrence is helping me out

16:53.142 --> 16:54.970
with some last-minute permits.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.581
We start construction on the
Children's Center in a week.

16:57.625 --> 17:01.411
And I want everything
to go according to plan.

17:01.455 --> 17:03.848
Is something wrong?

17:03.892 --> 17:05.981
- I don't know.

17:06.025 --> 17:08.505
- Something the two of you
want to tell me?

17:08.549 --> 17:10.246
- [chuckling]

17:10.290 --> 17:12.074
Your son came
to visit me yesterday.

17:12.118 --> 17:13.771
I'm sorry, I...

17:13.815 --> 17:15.077
got him worried about nothing.

17:15.121 --> 17:16.513
- Nothing?

17:16.557 --> 17:17.819
- I was having a bad day.

17:17.862 --> 17:19.429
On top of that I was having

17:19.473 --> 17:21.823
a ton of construction problems.

17:21.866 --> 17:22.911
It was a temporary setback.

17:22.954 --> 17:24.391
Look, I-I apologize.

17:24.434 --> 17:27.394
I should not have
dumped all my woes

17:27.437 --> 17:29.091
onto this young man.

17:29.135 --> 17:30.092
Don't worry about it, baby.

17:30.136 --> 17:31.093
I woke up this morning

17:31.137 --> 17:32.094
feeling like a champ.

17:32.138 --> 17:34.096
I went down there, boom!

17:34.140 --> 17:35.489
Got them straight at the bank.

17:35.532 --> 17:37.099
- But you said
that wasn't possible.

17:37.143 --> 17:38.579
- Well, that's exactly why

17:38.622 --> 17:40.581
I don't talk to y'all folks
about my business.

17:40.624 --> 17:42.757
Come on, you know I almost
lost this project

17:42.800 --> 17:45.107
a dozen times?
It's par for the course.

17:45.151 --> 17:48.763
I apologize
for all the dramatics.

17:48.806 --> 17:50.721
But I promise you.

17:50.765 --> 17:53.550
I promise you, I'm good.

17:55.639 --> 17:57.946
- I really think my uncle
is hiding something.

17:57.989 --> 18:00.775
- Why would he lie
about everything being okay?

18:00.818 --> 18:02.951
- I don't know.
Maybe he doesn't want my dad

18:02.994 --> 18:04.170
to know how bad things are.

18:04.213 --> 18:06.128
- Yeah, or maybe
he fixed everything.

18:06.172 --> 18:07.738
I mean, you said
he's a good businessman.

18:07.782 --> 18:09.131
- Yeah, she's right.

18:09.175 --> 18:10.219
Yesterday could have
just been about

18:10.263 --> 18:11.829
him feeling bad for himself.

18:11.873 --> 18:13.614
- No, no, I don't think so.

18:13.657 --> 18:15.094
- So what are you gonna do?

18:18.227 --> 18:20.403
- How hard would it be

18:20.447 --> 18:23.058
to dig into
my uncle's finances?

18:23.102 --> 18:25.016
Just to see what's going on
with his business?

18:25.060 --> 18:27.323
- On a scale of one to ten,

18:27.367 --> 18:28.542
like a two.

18:28.585 --> 18:29.543
- All right.

18:29.586 --> 18:30.848
- Miles.

18:30.892 --> 18:32.154
Are you sure?

18:32.198 --> 18:34.025
That's an incredible
breach of trust.

18:34.069 --> 18:35.244
- Cara, what other choice
do I have?

18:35.288 --> 18:36.637
Okay, if I find out that things

18:36.680 --> 18:38.160
have turned around
for him, great.

18:38.204 --> 18:39.944
But if they haven't,
I need to know

18:39.988 --> 18:42.077
what's really going on.

18:42.121 --> 18:44.297
- Okay.

18:44.340 --> 18:46.690
I gotta go to lunch, but
you'll text me what you find?

18:46.734 --> 18:47.735
- I'll walk you out.

18:47.778 --> 18:48.910
I have to head down

18:48.953 --> 18:50.738
to the groundbreaking ceremony.

18:50.781 --> 18:52.609
Yo, you can use my computer.

18:52.653 --> 18:56.004
If you find anything,
please call me.

18:56.047 --> 18:58.311
- Well, that's great, uh...

18:58.354 --> 19:00.443
I got nothing to do.

19:09.757 --> 19:11.802
- I thought we should...

19:11.846 --> 19:13.717
talk about things
before Cara arrives.

19:13.761 --> 19:15.937
- There's nothing
to talk about.

19:15.980 --> 19:18.200
If Cara wants to forgive
and forget, that's her choice.

19:18.244 --> 19:21.203
I can't stop her from having
a relationship with you.

19:21.247 --> 19:22.944
The only thing...

19:22.987 --> 19:24.685
I hope is that you
really have changed.

19:24.728 --> 19:26.208
- I have.

19:26.252 --> 19:28.428
If being sober
has taught me anything,

19:28.471 --> 19:30.647
it's the need for honesty.

19:30.691 --> 19:31.996
Jeffrey.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.824
Cara's finally
opening up to me.

19:33.868 --> 19:35.522
We could have
a real relationship.

19:35.565 --> 19:36.740
I can't jeopardize that

19:36.784 --> 19:38.481
by lying to her about the past.

19:38.525 --> 19:39.743
- You're not gonna
jeopardize anything

19:39.787 --> 19:42.355
because she's never
gonna find out.

19:42.398 --> 19:44.226
- Hey.

19:44.270 --> 19:45.227
Is everything okay?

19:45.271 --> 19:46.663
- Yeah, everything's fine.

19:46.707 --> 19:49.188
Let's eat.

19:52.234 --> 19:55.411
- So what looks good?

19:55.455 --> 19:56.717
- Not sure.

19:56.760 --> 19:59.589
- Me either.

20:02.244 --> 20:03.854
- So what were you guys
talking about

20:03.898 --> 20:05.987
before I came in?

20:07.771 --> 20:10.731
- Nothing.

20:10.774 --> 20:12.950
- Mom?

20:16.258 --> 20:17.303
Okay, well someone needs

20:17.346 --> 20:20.741
to tell me what's going on.

20:27.313 --> 20:30.968
- Look, Cara. Um...

20:31.012 --> 20:33.841
Things were difficult
after your mom left.

20:33.884 --> 20:35.625
And it was a long time

20:35.669 --> 20:38.106
before you were happy again.

20:38.149 --> 20:39.499
And one day, when you were

20:39.542 --> 20:40.500
in the eighth grade,

20:40.543 --> 20:42.197
she came back.

20:42.241 --> 20:45.331
- Yeah.

20:45.374 --> 20:47.115
Wait, how do you know that?

20:49.073 --> 20:53.034
- Because she came
to see me first.

20:56.167 --> 20:59.910
And she claimed that she had
stopped drinking

20:59.954 --> 21:04.263
and that she wanted to be
part of your life again.

21:04.306 --> 21:07.309
- And you told her no?

21:07.353 --> 21:08.615
How could you do that?

21:08.658 --> 21:09.964
- Because I had
heard it before.

21:10.007 --> 21:11.357
The promises to stop,

21:11.400 --> 21:14.360
the assurance that
things would be different.

21:14.403 --> 21:16.187
They never were.

21:16.231 --> 21:18.755
You--You don't remember
all the times

21:18.799 --> 21:20.627
she never came home.

21:20.670 --> 21:22.455
I do.

21:22.498 --> 21:25.066
And I knew that if she came
back into your life

21:25.109 --> 21:27.155
and left it again,
it would destroy you.

21:27.198 --> 21:29.244
- Yeah, well, that wasn't
your decision to make.

21:29.288 --> 21:30.724
It was mine.

21:30.767 --> 21:32.639
- I'm your father.
It was my job to protect you.

21:32.682 --> 21:34.118
- Oh, protect me?

21:34.162 --> 21:35.294
From what, the truth?

21:35.337 --> 21:36.469
- Cara. Listen.

21:36.512 --> 21:37.818
- No, no, no.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.341
You know, I spent
my entire life

21:39.385 --> 21:42.388
thinking that my mother
didn't want me.

21:42.431 --> 21:43.606
You know, that she didn't

21:43.650 --> 21:48.742
love me enough to even try.

21:48.785 --> 21:50.004
My whole life I thought that

21:50.047 --> 21:51.135
she was the cause of that pain

21:51.179 --> 21:52.223
but it turns out I was blaming

21:52.267 --> 21:55.096
the wrong parent.

21:56.663 --> 21:58.621
- Cara...

21:58.665 --> 22:02.016
♪

22:06.847 --> 22:08.370
- Uncle T.

22:08.414 --> 22:11.373
- Hey, hey, hey.
You showed up.

22:11.417 --> 22:12.592
Oh, I'm so glad
you could make it.

22:12.635 --> 22:13.854
It's a great day, all right?

22:13.897 --> 22:15.725
- I need you to be
straight with me.

22:15.769 --> 22:18.467
Is your business really okay?

22:18.511 --> 22:20.469
- Come on, I told you.
We're good.

22:20.513 --> 22:22.471
All right? The bank came
through with the loan.

22:22.515 --> 22:25.039
No need to worry
about this, all right?

22:25.082 --> 22:26.910
Just drop it.

22:26.954 --> 22:29.348
Enjoy this day.

22:33.047 --> 22:35.963
[phone buzzing]

22:36.006 --> 22:36.964
- Rakesh.

22:37.007 --> 22:38.313
Please tell me my uncle

22:38.357 --> 22:39.619
got that loan from the bank.

22:39.662 --> 22:41.098
- Not quite.

22:41.142 --> 22:42.665
He wired money out of

22:42.709 --> 22:44.972
the Harlem Episcopal Church's
bank account.

22:45.015 --> 22:47.627
Almost 600 grand.

22:47.670 --> 22:51.500
Maybe your dad lent him
the money?

22:51.544 --> 22:54.285
- No.

22:56.505 --> 22:58.638
No, he stole it.

23:06.515 --> 23:08.430
- Hey, baby boy.

23:08.474 --> 23:10.040
- So your idea

23:10.084 --> 23:11.651
of saving your dream

23:11.694 --> 23:13.261
is stealing from the church?

23:13.304 --> 23:14.436
How could you?

23:14.480 --> 23:15.568
- Man, what are you talking
about?

23:15.611 --> 23:16.873
Where you getting that from?

23:16.917 --> 23:18.179
- I know you transferred
that money

23:18.222 --> 23:19.398
from Harlem Episcopal.

23:19.441 --> 23:22.401
[tense music]

23:22.444 --> 23:26.448
♪

23:26.492 --> 23:27.797
- I know what it looks like.

23:27.841 --> 23:29.843
I know, I know what
it looks like.

23:29.886 --> 23:31.758
I know what it looks like,

23:31.801 --> 23:32.759
but it's just a loan.

23:32.802 --> 23:33.934
- A loan means someone

23:33.977 --> 23:34.978
lent you the money

23:35.022 --> 23:36.023
and we both know my father

23:36.066 --> 23:37.198
did not sign off on that.

23:37.241 --> 23:38.199
- Shh, do not do that
right now.

23:38.242 --> 23:39.200
Okay? It's no big deal.

23:39.243 --> 23:40.201
Listen to me. I'm going

23:40.244 --> 23:41.507
to put the money back

23:41.550 --> 23:43.030
before anybody even knows
it's missing.

23:43.073 --> 23:44.335
Okay?

23:44.379 --> 23:47.730
- Hey, guys.

23:47.774 --> 23:50.559
What's going on?

23:50.603 --> 23:52.431
- Tell him.

23:52.474 --> 23:55.521
Or I will.

23:55.564 --> 23:58.132
- Terrence?
- [sighs]

23:58.175 --> 24:01.396
Uh, my business had a little
financial hiccup

24:01.440 --> 24:03.790
and I needed to get
a little something

24:03.833 --> 24:07.446
to get my guys back to work.

24:07.489 --> 24:12.233
So... probably should have
asked you first,

24:12.276 --> 24:14.496
but I took a little loan
from the church.

24:14.540 --> 24:21.547
♪

24:24.071 --> 24:25.420
- You did what?

24:25.464 --> 24:27.030
- It's from
the Children's Center.

24:27.074 --> 24:29.468
The money is just sitting there
in an account.

24:29.511 --> 24:30.556
We don't have to make a payment

24:30.599 --> 24:31.948
until the end of the month.

24:31.992 --> 24:36.126
Okay? I will have it
back by then.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.651
- What were you thinking?

24:38.694 --> 24:42.306
- Do you trust me?
- Trust.

24:42.350 --> 24:45.309
You've already broken
that trust.

24:45.353 --> 24:47.790
With the board,
with the congregation,

24:47.834 --> 24:50.271
with the community--
- I understand that.

24:50.314 --> 24:52.099
But, look, I had to protect
my future.

24:52.142 --> 24:53.143
- Your future!

24:53.187 --> 24:54.275
- Arthur.

24:54.318 --> 24:55.450
I will fix this.

24:55.494 --> 24:56.495
- No. You know what, see,

24:56.538 --> 24:57.496
I've heard that before.

24:57.539 --> 24:58.540
You know what?

24:58.584 --> 25:00.020
You have actually left me

25:00.063 --> 25:01.587
with no choice.

25:01.630 --> 25:03.240
Because I have to tell
the board everything.

25:03.284 --> 25:04.459
- Then I'll go to jail, and--

25:04.503 --> 25:05.547
- No, no. Dad, Dad, Dad.

25:05.591 --> 25:07.157
Let's talk about this.

25:07.201 --> 25:08.985
Maybe we can figure
something out together.

25:09.029 --> 25:11.074
- Could you listen
to your son, please? Okay?

25:11.118 --> 25:12.815
Arthur, if you do that,

25:12.859 --> 25:14.382
they might blame you.
- I am well aware

25:14.425 --> 25:15.775
of the consequences.

25:15.818 --> 25:17.603
I just wish to God
that you had been.

25:17.646 --> 25:22.477
♪

25:22.521 --> 25:24.218
- Miles, I know I messed up.

25:24.261 --> 25:25.480
Look, I'm gonna
make this right.

25:25.524 --> 25:26.742
I'm gonna get
the money back.

25:26.786 --> 25:27.787
- How?

25:27.830 --> 25:28.875
You said there was no bank

25:28.918 --> 25:30.137
that would give you a loan.

25:30.180 --> 25:32.705
- I know.
There are other options.

25:32.748 --> 25:33.880
[sighing] I just need

25:33.923 --> 25:35.490
a little more time.

25:35.534 --> 25:36.709
Can you just talk
to your father

25:36.752 --> 25:37.797
and calm him down?

25:37.840 --> 25:38.798
- I-I...

25:38.841 --> 25:40.451
- Miles.

25:40.495 --> 25:43.498
You've always had faith in me.

25:43.542 --> 25:47.023
Don't lose it now.

25:47.067 --> 25:50.026
[gentle piano music]

25:50.070 --> 25:56.467
♪

25:58.208 --> 25:59.558
- Let me guess, you're here

25:59.601 --> 26:02.169
to plead your uncle's case.
- No.

26:02.212 --> 26:04.737
No, I'm worried about him,
but...

26:04.780 --> 26:06.695
I'm not here to defend
his actions.

26:06.739 --> 26:08.523
I still can't believe he
would do something like this.

26:08.567 --> 26:10.481
- Yeah, well, I wish
I could say the same.

26:10.525 --> 26:13.354
- Wait, what do you mean?

26:13.397 --> 26:14.616
- A few years back,
he was trying

26:14.660 --> 26:16.009
to get another project
off the ground,

26:16.052 --> 26:17.880
and I discovered
that he had taken a loan

26:17.924 --> 26:20.361
from the church.
It wasn't a lot of money.

26:20.404 --> 26:22.624
He put it back before
anyone else found out.

26:22.668 --> 26:23.843
Of course I confronted him

26:23.886 --> 26:25.105
and he said it was just,
you know,

26:25.148 --> 26:26.715
a lapse of judgment that

26:26.759 --> 26:29.675
would never happen again.

26:29.718 --> 26:31.415
I believed him.

26:31.459 --> 26:32.765
[chuckling sadly]

26:32.808 --> 26:36.072
So.
- You didn't say anything.

26:40.294 --> 26:41.382
- You know,

26:41.425 --> 26:42.601
you are not the only one

26:42.644 --> 26:43.732
that loves him, Miles.

26:43.776 --> 26:44.907
- Right, but, Dad,

26:44.951 --> 26:45.952
if you go to the board

26:45.995 --> 26:47.388
Uncle T could go to jail.

26:47.431 --> 26:48.432
- Mm-hmm.
- And you could

26:48.476 --> 26:49.695
lose everything.
- Mm-hmm.

26:49.738 --> 26:52.306
- So please, please.

26:52.349 --> 26:54.743
Just give him some time
to put the money back.

26:54.787 --> 26:56.179
He always comes through.

26:56.223 --> 26:58.138
- I'm sorry, Miles.
I am not going to repeat

26:58.181 --> 27:00.619
past mistakes,
and I have to honor the faith

27:00.662 --> 27:02.359
that my congregation
placed in me.

27:02.403 --> 27:04.840
No matter the outcome.

27:04.884 --> 27:11.891
♪

27:14.502 --> 27:16.678
- So what are you gonna do?

27:16.722 --> 27:19.159
- No idea.

27:19.202 --> 27:20.682
What are you gonna do?

27:20.726 --> 27:23.598
- No idea.

27:23.642 --> 27:26.166
I never should have insisted
on that stupid lunch.

27:26.209 --> 27:31.301
- Yeah, because now you'll
never look at him the same.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.521
- You think your uncle
will ever get that money back?

27:33.564 --> 27:34.783
- I don't know how.

27:34.827 --> 27:36.959
He's desperate.

27:37.003 --> 27:39.092
He said something
about another option.

27:39.135 --> 27:41.007
And what if he's gonna do
something he shouldn't?

27:41.050 --> 27:42.138
- I mean, what could be worse
than stealing from the church?

27:42.182 --> 27:43.836
- I don't know.

27:43.879 --> 27:45.707
I just wish I knew what
was going on in his head.

27:45.751 --> 27:47.404
- I mean, you could
talk to your Aunt Lena.

27:47.448 --> 27:48.884
- No.
- Trust me,

27:48.928 --> 27:51.670
spouses keep secrets
they don't tell anyone else.

27:51.713 --> 27:53.367
- [sighs] Yeah, you're right.

27:53.410 --> 27:54.716
And she's heading upstate.

27:54.760 --> 27:56.500
I need to catch her
before she goes.

27:56.544 --> 28:01.592
♪

28:01.636 --> 28:04.378
Hey, I know that
you're mad at your dad,

28:04.421 --> 28:07.337
but sometimes
we would do anything

28:07.381 --> 28:08.861
to protect the ones we love.

28:08.904 --> 28:12.908
♪

28:12.952 --> 28:14.910
I'll talk to you later.

28:22.222 --> 28:23.440
- Oh, Miles?

28:23.484 --> 28:25.051
What are you doing here?
- Lena.

28:25.094 --> 28:26.487
I need to talk to you.

28:26.530 --> 28:28.097
Uncle T is in trouble

28:28.141 --> 28:29.882
and I need your help.

28:29.925 --> 28:31.492
He took money from the church

28:31.535 --> 28:33.755
and he can't pay it back.

28:33.799 --> 28:37.237
He's done it once before.

28:37.280 --> 28:38.934
- I know.

28:38.978 --> 28:41.371
It was when he was
just starting his business.

28:41.415 --> 28:42.503
But he put it all back.

28:42.546 --> 28:43.765
- How?

28:43.809 --> 28:45.419
Where did he get
the money from?

28:45.462 --> 28:48.465
- An old business associate.

28:48.509 --> 28:50.032
He's not the kind of guy
you want to

28:50.076 --> 28:51.207
borrow money from.

28:51.251 --> 28:53.035
But thankfully it wasn't much.

28:53.079 --> 28:54.863
And he paid him back
before things got dangerous.

28:54.907 --> 28:57.648
- This time he borrowed
more than just a little.

28:57.692 --> 29:00.782
I need to know who
he borrowed the money from.

29:00.826 --> 29:02.349
- His name's Conrad Taylor.

29:02.392 --> 29:05.221
He lives in the neighborhood,
but...

29:05.265 --> 29:06.570
I don't know where he is.

29:06.614 --> 29:07.571
- I think I do.

29:07.615 --> 29:08.964
- Wait. Miles.

29:09.008 --> 29:10.357
If he's desperate enough to

29:10.400 --> 29:11.445
take money from Conrad again

29:11.488 --> 29:13.186
he's not gonna listen to you.

29:13.229 --> 29:17.059
♪

29:17.103 --> 29:18.408
- Listen to me, Terrence.

29:18.452 --> 29:19.758
If you go down this road,

29:19.801 --> 29:22.717
there may be no turning back.

29:22.761 --> 29:26.373
Are you sure
you want to do this?

29:26.416 --> 29:28.505
- What choice do I have?

29:37.166 --> 29:39.952
- There he is.

29:41.301 --> 29:42.519
- Reverend.

29:42.563 --> 29:43.869
- Conrad. You mind if I, uh,

29:43.912 --> 29:45.131
have a word with
my brother-in-law?

29:45.174 --> 29:48.351
Alone?
- Not at all.

29:48.395 --> 29:55.402
♪

29:56.751 --> 29:57.708
- I gotta do it, Arthur.

29:57.752 --> 29:58.927
I gotta make this right.

29:58.971 --> 30:00.276
- Not like this.
Borrowing money

30:00.320 --> 30:02.757
from a man like Conrad
is not the answer.

30:02.801 --> 30:03.802
You don't pay him back--

30:03.845 --> 30:05.804
- I know how this goes.

30:05.847 --> 30:08.415
It's the only thing I can fix.

30:08.458 --> 30:12.201
- Uncle T.

30:12.245 --> 30:13.986
Do you remember the promise
you made to me

30:14.029 --> 30:16.118
after my mom died?

30:16.162 --> 30:18.642
You said that no matter
what happens

30:18.686 --> 30:20.862
you would never leave me.

30:20.906 --> 30:23.865
That family was a bond
that could not be broken.

30:23.909 --> 30:26.694
And that no matter what...

30:26.737 --> 30:29.131
we would figure it out
together.

30:29.175 --> 30:31.873
Now are you gonna break
that promise to me?

30:31.917 --> 30:35.964
To my dad? To Ali?

30:36.008 --> 30:39.881
To Auntie Lena?

30:39.925 --> 30:44.190
We need you, Uncle T.

30:44.233 --> 30:45.931
- What about the money?

30:45.974 --> 30:48.629
- The only thing that matters
is where we go from here.

30:48.672 --> 30:50.979
But we can't do that until
you get up out of that chair

30:51.023 --> 30:53.852
and walk through that door
with us.

30:53.895 --> 30:56.593
♪

30:56.637 --> 30:58.421
- Please, Uncle T.

30:58.465 --> 31:04.427
♪

31:04.471 --> 31:06.560
- Hey.
- Hey.

31:09.476 --> 31:11.521
Thanks for meeting me.

31:11.565 --> 31:14.785
- Yeah, well, you're not
the one who lied.

31:14.829 --> 31:17.353
- Cara, he was trying
to protect you.

31:17.397 --> 31:19.834
- Yeah, well, it should have
been my decision.

31:19.878 --> 31:21.792
- I understand.

31:21.836 --> 31:24.273
But you have one to make now.

31:24.317 --> 31:25.579
You can either live in the past

31:25.622 --> 31:27.407
or decide to move forward.

31:27.450 --> 31:28.712
- You know, he's always been

31:28.756 --> 31:30.845
the one person
that I can count on.

31:30.889 --> 31:35.241
That I could trust
to always put me first.

31:35.284 --> 31:36.938
I mean, growing up
he was my hero,

31:36.982 --> 31:39.158
but now it's like...

31:39.201 --> 31:43.423
it's like I don't even know
who he is anymore.

31:43.466 --> 31:45.729
- All right,
I'm gonna say something,

31:45.773 --> 31:48.732
and I really hope you don't
take it the wrong way.

31:48.776 --> 31:52.040
But in the spirit
of total honesty...

31:52.084 --> 31:53.215
that's ridiculous.

31:53.259 --> 31:54.260
- What?

31:54.303 --> 31:55.870
- Your father is the same man

31:55.914 --> 31:57.350
you've always known.

31:57.393 --> 31:58.351
The same man who was left

31:58.394 --> 31:59.352
to raise a little girl

31:59.395 --> 32:01.136
in an impossible situation.

32:01.180 --> 32:02.964
- Why are you defending him?

32:03.008 --> 32:04.009
- Because he was strong enough

32:04.052 --> 32:08.970
to do something I couldn't.

32:09.014 --> 32:11.842
I've been granted
a second chance

32:11.886 --> 32:14.062
to get to know
an amazing young woman

32:14.106 --> 32:19.372
who I'm lucky enough
to call my daughter.

32:19.415 --> 32:22.331
You said he was your hero.

32:22.375 --> 32:23.811
Heroes have it easy.

32:23.854 --> 32:26.379
Heroes aren't real.

32:26.422 --> 32:29.686
Being a dad?

32:29.730 --> 32:31.993
That's real.

32:32.037 --> 32:35.170
♪

32:35.214 --> 32:38.217
- Have you spoken to Uncle T?

32:38.260 --> 32:40.088
- I've been a little busy
trying to figure out

32:40.132 --> 32:43.439
a way out of the mess
that he made.

32:43.483 --> 32:45.311
- Is there a way out?

32:45.354 --> 32:47.530
- Honestly, I'm not sure.

32:47.574 --> 32:52.013
I mean, if I can give
the board assurances

32:52.057 --> 32:54.450
that the money will be
back in the account

32:54.494 --> 32:56.104
before we break ground,

32:56.148 --> 32:59.020
then maybe I can persuade them
not to press charges

32:59.064 --> 33:02.458
against... Terrence.
- Wait, what...

33:02.502 --> 33:05.200
What assurances?

33:05.244 --> 33:08.116
And how do you plan
to replace the money?

33:15.863 --> 33:17.952
- You're sitting in it.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.563
- You're gonna sell the house?

33:20.607 --> 33:23.131
No. No, you can't do that.

33:23.175 --> 33:24.872
There has to be another way.

33:24.915 --> 33:26.526
- There isn't.

33:26.569 --> 33:28.267
And I won't send your uncle
to prison.

33:28.310 --> 33:31.052
Let's just hope...

33:31.096 --> 33:33.446
the board feels the same way.

33:36.797 --> 33:38.233
I've got to get down there.

33:38.277 --> 33:42.107
- You mind if I tag along?

33:42.150 --> 33:44.152
- I'd like that.

33:44.196 --> 33:51.159
♪

33:51.203 --> 33:57.209
Um... thank you
for meeting with me.

33:57.252 --> 34:00.473
I stand before you
with a heavy heart.

34:00.516 --> 34:03.128
Something has come
to my attention that I think--

34:03.171 --> 34:04.694
- Sorry I'm late.

34:04.738 --> 34:06.305
[clears throat]

34:06.348 --> 34:10.570
♪

34:10.613 --> 34:11.658
- What are you doing here?

34:11.701 --> 34:14.356
- Fixing this.

34:14.400 --> 34:21.407
♪

34:22.538 --> 34:23.800
- Reverend Finer
has asked you all

34:23.844 --> 34:26.107
to meet here today to...

34:26.151 --> 34:30.459
inform you that...

34:30.503 --> 34:33.114
I've embezzled money
from the church.

34:33.158 --> 34:35.464
[concerned murmuring]

34:35.508 --> 34:37.814
And my brother-in-law
had no knowledge

34:37.858 --> 34:39.947
of anything I've done.

34:39.990 --> 34:43.124
I take full responsibility.

34:43.168 --> 34:46.736
So if you...

34:46.780 --> 34:51.437
want to press charges,
then I completely understand.

34:51.480 --> 34:56.006
And I will be, um, cooperative.

34:56.050 --> 35:00.881
But before that, I just ask
that you look at this.

35:00.924 --> 35:02.883
You'll see that all the funds

35:02.926 --> 35:04.145
have been returned
to the account.

35:04.189 --> 35:05.538
Now, this does not excuse

35:05.581 --> 35:08.062
my poor behavior,

35:08.106 --> 35:11.370
nor replace the trust

35:11.413 --> 35:13.372
that you all
have instilled in me.

35:13.415 --> 35:16.375
But at least it's a step

35:16.418 --> 35:20.422
toward making amends.

35:20.466 --> 35:23.164
- Arthur.

35:23.208 --> 35:24.905
We'd like a moment

35:24.948 --> 35:29.301
to continue to discuss this
further with Terrence.

35:29.344 --> 35:30.737
Would you mind waiting outside?

35:30.780 --> 35:32.695
- No.

35:32.739 --> 35:36.917
♪

35:43.793 --> 35:45.186
- Well, the board decided

35:45.230 --> 35:48.363
they don't want
to press charges.

35:48.407 --> 35:51.105
And they don't want to hold you
accountable for

35:51.149 --> 35:53.934
my stupid ass mistake.

35:53.977 --> 35:54.935
- How did you replace
the money?

35:54.978 --> 35:55.936
And please don't tell me

35:55.979 --> 35:57.155
that you went to Conrad.

35:57.198 --> 36:00.941
- No.
- Then how'd you get it?

36:03.900 --> 36:05.511
- I sold my last little

36:05.554 --> 36:06.512
remaining stake in the complex

36:06.555 --> 36:08.775
back to the bank.

36:08.818 --> 36:09.906
Guess I should have done that

36:09.950 --> 36:11.299
a long time ago.

36:11.343 --> 36:14.824
Arthur, I'm sorry.

36:14.868 --> 36:16.304
I just hope you can find it

36:16.348 --> 36:21.353
in your heart to forgive me.

36:25.792 --> 36:28.534
The board wants to talk to you.

36:28.577 --> 36:33.756
- "Happy are they whose
transgressions are forgiven."

36:37.195 --> 36:38.413
- I'm proud of you, Uncle T.

36:38.457 --> 36:41.938
You know, you did
the right thing.

36:41.982 --> 36:43.462
You gonna be okay?

36:43.505 --> 36:45.464
- I've just been so focused on

36:45.507 --> 36:46.900
getting my seat at the table,

36:46.943 --> 36:49.207
I forgot that I already had one

36:49.250 --> 36:50.599
with the people
that count the most.

36:50.643 --> 36:53.123
- Yeah, but you still
do, Uncle T.

36:53.167 --> 36:54.734
- I sure hope you're right.

36:54.777 --> 36:57.302
- So what's next?

36:57.345 --> 37:00.043
- Uh, I'm gonna go upstate.

37:00.087 --> 37:02.655
See my wife.

37:02.698 --> 37:04.047
I'm gonna convince her
I'm still

37:04.091 --> 37:05.266
the man that she married.

37:05.310 --> 37:09.879
♪

37:09.923 --> 37:12.317
Look, I, uh...

37:12.360 --> 37:14.754
I know you've always looked up
to me as a father figure

37:14.797 --> 37:15.885
but let me tell you something.

37:15.929 --> 37:19.237
You got a great man in there.

37:19.280 --> 37:23.284
So I think it's time
you start looking to him.

37:23.328 --> 37:26.809
And whoever started this
God account, you should...

37:26.853 --> 37:29.899
if you ever find out,
you thank them for me.

37:29.943 --> 37:31.945
And let them know
that they chose

37:31.988 --> 37:35.122
the right man.

37:35.165 --> 37:36.515
I love you, boy.
Come here.

37:36.558 --> 37:38.995
- I love you too, Uncle T.

37:39.039 --> 37:46.046
♪

37:49.354 --> 37:51.094
- So what's the plan?

37:51.138 --> 37:52.835
I thought none of your contacts
knew where Falken is.

37:52.879 --> 37:54.489
How are we gonna find him?

37:54.533 --> 37:56.665
- Pop that in for me.

37:56.709 --> 37:57.753
- Okay.

37:57.797 --> 38:03.542
♪

38:03.585 --> 38:04.543
That's, ah,

38:04.586 --> 38:05.805
that's the piece of

38:05.848 --> 38:06.806
the God account code
I sent you.

38:06.849 --> 38:08.111
- Exactly.

38:08.155 --> 38:09.461
We use it as bait.

38:09.504 --> 38:10.462
You want to find Falken?

38:10.505 --> 38:11.506
Post it on the Internet.

38:11.550 --> 38:13.160
Lure him out of whatever hole

38:13.203 --> 38:14.161
he's been hiding in.

38:14.204 --> 38:15.554
- Make him come to us.

38:15.597 --> 38:16.555
- You ready for this?

38:16.598 --> 38:17.991
- Launch it.

38:18.034 --> 38:24.084
♪

38:24.127 --> 38:25.564
- Going somewhere?

38:30.612 --> 38:33.180
- I guess that's up to you.

38:33.223 --> 38:37.053
- You lied to me.

38:37.097 --> 38:39.317
- I know.

38:39.360 --> 38:41.536
I'm sorry.

38:43.364 --> 38:46.672
I told myself that I was
trying to protect you.

38:46.715 --> 38:49.936
But the truth is...

38:49.979 --> 38:51.329
- What?

38:51.372 --> 38:53.679
- I was protecting myself.

38:53.722 --> 38:55.115
After your mother left,

38:55.158 --> 38:56.943
I didn't know if I could go on.

38:56.986 --> 38:58.248
For all the anger I felt.

38:58.292 --> 39:00.555
But more than that, I...

39:00.599 --> 39:02.775
I felt so alone.

39:02.818 --> 39:04.516
And terrified at the thought

39:04.559 --> 39:06.953
of raising a little girl
on my own.

39:06.996 --> 39:08.476
- I'm sorry.

39:08.520 --> 39:11.087
- No, don't be sorry.

39:11.131 --> 39:14.961
That look from my little girl
is what got me through it.

39:15.004 --> 39:17.790
Wanting to be invincible
for you.

39:17.833 --> 39:21.271
- I don't need you
to be that anymore.

39:21.315 --> 39:23.622
- I know.

39:23.665 --> 39:30.672
♪

39:32.195 --> 39:33.806
- I can't believe you were
willing to do that

39:33.849 --> 39:35.808
for Uncle T, Dad.

39:35.851 --> 39:38.941
- Well, it was a price
I was willing to pay.

39:38.985 --> 39:41.683
Besides...
[clears throat]

39:41.727 --> 39:45.513
I owe him a debt.

39:45.557 --> 39:48.124
- Uh, what debt?

39:48.168 --> 39:50.866
- After your mother died

39:50.910 --> 39:55.828
I thought seriously about
leaving the ministry.

39:55.871 --> 39:59.179
I still believed in God,

39:59.222 --> 40:00.833
but being able to believe,

40:00.876 --> 40:04.140
uh, and stand
at that pulpit on Sunday

40:04.184 --> 40:06.229
and preach and tell people

40:06.273 --> 40:09.189
that everything was okay?

40:09.232 --> 40:11.191
I wasn't sure I could.

40:11.234 --> 40:13.846
So I prayed.

40:13.889 --> 40:16.370
And I prayed.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.546
And one day
while I was praying,

40:18.590 --> 40:21.244
your uncle walked in.

40:21.288 --> 40:24.683
And I told him
all of this, and...

40:24.726 --> 40:27.120
bared my soul.

40:27.163 --> 40:30.515
And you know what he said?

40:30.558 --> 40:32.255
"Fake it until you make it."

40:32.299 --> 40:33.474
[both laughing]

40:33.518 --> 40:35.041
- He did not.

40:35.084 --> 40:36.738
- He most certainly did.
"Fake it until you make it."

40:36.782 --> 40:38.914
But...

40:38.958 --> 40:40.786
It was sage advice.

40:40.829 --> 40:42.701
He told me I had
to go back up there

40:42.744 --> 40:46.661
and if I started feeling lost

40:46.705 --> 40:48.881
or angry,

40:48.924 --> 40:51.666
that I should look down

40:51.710 --> 40:54.408
and he would be right there.

40:54.452 --> 40:57.890
♪

40:57.933 --> 41:00.545
And every Sunday

41:00.588 --> 41:03.199
from that day forward

